<br />
True, there are few solo endeavors that are truly challenging and reward tangible benefits. You can solo old raids (some guy just soloed Sha in the Terrace of endless Spring) - that's very challenging, but you won't get a character upgrade from doing so.<br />
But if you venture into 10 or 25 man territory, there's plenty of challenge to be had.<br />
<br />
I still consider the post a marketing ploy to get a hold of the people who already have decided that &quot;lulz wow is too easy, I need a challenging game!&quot;. All while having not a single heroic raid kill under their belt.
