		<div class="postbody">
			<div class="postrow">
				
				
				<h2 class="title icon icon0">
					Re: WoW lead dev: We killed MMO genre
				</h2>
				

						
						
				<div class="content">
					<div id="post_message_1786201">
						<blockquote class="postcontent restore ">
							I think the game that's come the closest to making exploration count is guild wars 2, but that they went about it in the wrong way. <br />
<br />
My ideas for a game that I think would encompass that:<br />
<br />
-do away with the leveling system<br />
-world that is huge with lots to explore<br />
-gain abilities through exploration<br />
-do away with classes (character is defined by abilities they chose andcan mix and match at will)<br />
-make it where you can become powerful with a broad variety of abilities<br />
<br />
The idea should be that there is so much to see and do in the world that its not something everybody is just willing to do, but balance that with being able to feel like you've made significant progress without habing seen the entire world. <br />
<br />
For example make a set of guard skills that a player could progress though the starting city and feel like a well developed character for city fighting without ever leaving town. Maybe that guy has no skill whatsoever to survive outside the city though. If he wants to be a Mage he can join the mages guild there and they'll send him all over tplace learning new skills, and in transit he learns the basics for living in the wild too, but not as much as say a ranger that spends his entire playtime living in the wilderness. <br />
<br />
I guess the ideal is a world too big to do everything but where you can feel accomplished no matter which things you choose to do. Modern mmos have too much emphasis on everyone being able to do everything so no developed content is wasted on an elite few, which makes sense but at the same time is definitely lowering the bar for what it takes to see the content. <br />
<br />
I don't want to show off by completing a harder version of the fight that everyone has done for a slightly higher number on a piece of gear. I want to show up in the city with a sword with a cool graphic from some abandoned hidden city that only a few people have ever seen. <br />
<br />
And the people that haven't seen my lost city can stand by me showing off the robes they were given for saving the son of a dragon king in the heart of a dragon city where I've never been because I'm KOS since I killed my first dragon months ago.
						</blockquote>
					</div>

					
				</div>
			</div>
			
			<div class="cleardiv"></div>
		</div>
	</div>
		<div class="postfoot">
